goal.ch:
"The focus of this 2-semesters-course is to introduce methodology for designing and developing technical products, and concerned with the problem formulation, the conceptual and the embodiment stage of design, rather than detail deign. 
The course is intended to provide you:
Some new but important concepts for innovation and product design, e.g., design thinking, interaction design;
General procedure of product design and development, and also methodical steps, from clarifying and specifying tasks, to finding and selecting solutions, until implementing the developed concepts based on marketing view point.
A set of tools and methods for product design and development;
Integration of important parameters in creating a new product (e.g. marketing, finance, engineering, production, quality control etc.)"

